{{Location map-line|lat=83}}
{{kml}}
The '''83rd parallel north''' is a [[circle of latitude]] that is 83 [[degree (angle)|degrees]] [[true north|north]] of the [[Earth|Earth's]] [[equator|equatorial plane]], in the [[Arctic]]. It passes through the [[Arctic Ocean]] and  [[North America]].

The [[Extreme points of Earth#Latitude and longitude|northernmost]] land on earth, whether the permanent [[Kaffeklubben Island]] or the shifting/resubmerging [[Bar (river morphology)|gravel banks]] of [[Oodaaq]], [[ATOW1996]], or [[83-42]] are roughly 40 [[Minute_of_arc#Cartography|minutes of arc]] (75 to 79 kilometres) north of this parallel.  

==Around the world==
Starting at the [[Prime Meridian]] and heading eastwards, the parallel 83° north passes through:

