{{lowercase}} '''iTyphoon''' is a mobile application that provides free typhoon updates to [[Filipinos]] and the world.<ref name="iTyphoonLaunched">{{cite web | url=http://www.nueca.net/ityphoon/2011/12/15/ityphoon-launched-in-quezon-city-philippines/ | title=iTyphoon Launched in Quezon City | publisher=[http://nueca.net Nueva Caceres Technology Solutions, Inc.] (Philippines) | accessdate=June 6, 2012}}</ref> It was developed by Magno Edilberto R. Conag III, president and C.E.O. of Nueva Caceres Technology Solutions, Inc., together with his friend, David Michael V. Padua, owner of Typhoon2000.com. The application is used by residents of Naga, Camarines Sur, in the Philippines to receive typhoon alerts and is available for use globally.<ref name="NagaiTyphoon">{{cite web | url=http://naga.gov.ph/news/naga-city%E2%80%99s-ityphoon-launched/ | title=Naga City’s iTyphoon Launched | publisher=[http://naga.gov.ph City Government of Naga] (Philippines) | author=Barrameda, Shiena M. | accessdate=January 16, 2012}}</ref> iTyphoon is available for iOS,<ref name="iTyphoonforiOS">{{cite web | url=http://www.nueca.net/ityphoon/2011/10/08/ityphoon-for-ios-out-now/ | title=iTyphoon for iOS Out Now | publisher=[http://nueca.net Nueva Caceres Technology Solutions, Inc.] (Philippines) | accessdate=June 6, 2012}}</ref> Android,<ref name="iTyphoonforAndroid">{{cite web | url=http://www.nueca.net/ityphoon/2011/12/24/ityphoon-version-1-4-released/ | title=iTyphoon v1.4 for Android Released | publisher=[http://nueca.net Nueva Caceres Technology Solutions, Inc.] (Philippines) | accessdate=June 6, 2012}}</ref> Nokia<ref name="iTyphoonforNokia">{{cite web | url=http://www.nueca.net/ityphoon/2012/05/22/ityphoon-now-available-for-nokia-series-40-devices/ | title=iTyphoon Now Available for Nokia Series 40 Feature Phones| publisher=[http://nueca.net Nueva Caceres Technology Solutions, Inc.] (Philippines) | accessdate=June 6, 2012}}</ref> Series 40, and is planned for Windows Phone and Qt.
