{{Infobox landform | name = Knivskjellodden | other_name = Knivskjelodden | image = Nordkapp09.jpg | image_size = | caption = Knivskjellodden as viewed from [[North Cape, Norway|North Cape]] | map_image = Nordkapp map.png | map_size = | map_caption = | location = [[Finnmark]], [[Norway]] | water_bodies = [[Barents Sea]] | coordinates = {{coord|71|11|08|N|25|40|54|E|type:landmark_region:NO|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | elevation = | area = | references = }}
'''Knivskjellodden''' or '''Knivskjelodden''' is a [[peninsula]] located in [[Nordkapp Municipality]] in [[Finnmark]] county, [[Norway]]. It is the northernmost point on the island of [[Magerøya]] in [[Northern Norway]]. It is sometimes considered the [[extreme points of Europe|northernmost point of the entire continent of Europe]]. The nearby [[Kinnarodden]] on the [[Nordkinn Peninsula]] is the northernmost point on the mainland.<ref name="snl">{{cite web|url=http://snl.no/Knivskjelodden|title=Knivskjelodden|author=Store norske leksikon|authorlink=Store norske leksikon|language=Norwegian|accessdate=2013-02-13}}</ref> The northernmost point of the country Norway is in fact [[Rossøya]], in [[Svalbard]], far north.
Knivskjellodden can only be reached on foot, after a {{convert|9|km|adj=on}} long hike from a parking area near the [[European route E69]] highway ({{coord|71.122|25.71}}), {{convert|6|km|abbr=on}} south of [[North Cape, Norway|North Cape]].
Travel agencies that organize trips for unaware tourists often advertise the [[North Cape, Norway|North Cape]] as the northern extremity of Europe, but this is not true as the Knivskjellodden is {{convert|1450|m}} further north.
==See also== *[[Lindesnes]], southernmost point in Norway *[[Extreme points of Europe]]
