{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2015}} [[File:Pensthorpe Nature Reserve -near Fakenham -Norfolk-30May2009.jpg|thumb|Pensthorpe Natural Park]] [[File:Pensthorpe Nature Reserve -near Fakenham -Norfolk-26oct2005.JPG|right|thumb|A view across a lake]] '''Pensthorpe Natural Park''' is located in [[Kettlestone|Pensthorpe]], [[Norfolk]], [[England]] and is approximately one mile from [[Fakenham]] and close to the [[A1067 road]]. The park covers {{convert|700|acres}}. The [[River Wensum]], which runs through the site, is a designated [[Special Area of Conservation]] (SAC).<ref name="SAC">{{cite web | url=http://jncc.defra.gov.uk/ProtectedSites/SACselection/sac.asp?EUCode=UK0012647 | title=SAC | publisher=jncc | accessdate=1 July 2012}}</ref>
Pensthorpe Conservation Trust (PCT) was formed in January 2003. It is a charitable trust that works closely with Pensthorpe Natural Park to showcase the importance of species and habitat conservation. The PCT works with partner organisations in national conservation programmes to conserve wetland and farmland bird species. These partnerships include Operation Turtle Dove, The Great Crane Project and re-introduction projects for [[Red squirrel|red squirrels]] and [[Corncrake|corncrakes]].
== History == The site was created as a nature reserve by Bill Makins in the 1980s, before being bought by Bill and Deb Jordan in 2003, of [[Jordans (company)|Jordans cereals]]. During excavations to create the lakes and wader scrapes, one million tons of aggregates were excavated. The work uncovered finds including a [[hand axe]] believed to date from 8000 BC. Tusks and the tooth from a [[woolly mammoth]] were also found.<ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/norfolk/content/articles/2008/06/12/places_wensum_valley_20080612_feature.shtml] BBC Norfolk video tour Retrieved 24 October 2008</ref>
==Media==
The reserve was the location of the [[BBC]] programme ''[[Springwatch]]'' from May 2008 to 2010.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/local/norfolk/hi/people_and_places/nature/newsid_8563000/8563186.stm BBC news item] Retrieved 10 June 2010</ref><ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/norfolk/content/articles/2008/06/11/springwatch_pensthorpe_return_feature.shtml Springwatch 2009] Retrieved 9 May 2009</ref>
First broadcast in December 2013, the first episode of the [[BBC]] television series ''[[Great British Garden Revival]]'' was based in the reserve.<ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/profiles/41ttbPVvt5kCyhyVfGVKTtq/monty-don Great British Garden Revival] Retrieved 28 September 2014</ref>
