{{Infobox artwork/wikidata|location=[[Rijksmuseum]]}}
'''''The Oude Stadhuis in Amsterdam''''' is a 1657 painting by [[Pieter Jansz. Saenredam]], based on a drawing he made of the Old Town Hall on [[Dam Square]] over six days in 1641 before its demolition. It was bought from the painter in 1658 for 300 guilders by the mayor of Amsterdam for his office in the [[Royal Palace of Amsterdam|New Town Hall]]. It is now in the city's [[Rijksmuseum]].

